# RetroRapid — Core Swift Standards

Full conventions: see `@AGENTS.md` (repo root) and the `retrorapid-conventions` skill.
For SwiftUI, concurrency, accessibility, and testing patterns — use the applicable skill (`swiftui-expert-skill`, `swift-concurrency`, `ios-accessibility`, `swift-testing-expert`).

## Critical Rules

- Route behavior through `Requirements/INDEX.md`; keep the app compiling after every change.
- Protocol-based DI — no default instantiations in `init` for business dependencies.
- Share platform-agnostic logic in `RetroRacingShared/`; no `#if os()` in service layer.
- All user-facing strings in `Localizable.xcstrings`.
- Never force-unwrap; use safe unwrapping patterns.
- Use `@Observable` — not `ObservableObject`.
- Run unit tests after code changes.

## Code Style

- Top-level methods read like a table of contents; delegate to well-named helpers.
- ~200 lines of production code per file (exclude `#Preview` blocks).
- Comments explain **why**, not what.
